-- Mobius Says China Yuan Exchange Reform Hasn't Made Stocks More Attractive
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-22T23:57:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/mobius-says-china-yuan-exchange-reform-hasn-t-make-stocks-more-attractive.html

          
          
             China’s decision to make its
currency more flexible hasn’t made its stock market more
attractive as there won’t be a significant gain in the yuan and
any change will be gradual, Templeton Asset Management Ltd.’s
Mark Mobius said in e-mailed comments.  
